docs.abstract: Thierry Bolloré was dismissed after Nissan named a new chief. The automakers are part of an alliance once led by the ousted Carlos Ghosn.
docs.snippet: Thierry Bolloré was dismissed after Nissan named a new chief. The automakers are part of an alliance once led by the ousted Carlos Ghosn.
docs.lead_paragraph: Renault’s board fired its chief executive, Thierry Bolloré, on Friday, just days after Nissan shook up its leadership as the two automakers in a much-vaunted alliance struggle to regain their footing nearly a year after Carlos Ghosn was ousted as their chairman.

headline.main: Renault Fires Its C.E.O., as the Post-Ghosn Shake-Up Continues
headline.print_headline: Renault Ousts Its Chief Days After Nissan Appoints Leader in Post-Ghosn Era

docs.abstract: The swelling market for property technology to help buy, sell and manage properties has attracted building owners as well as venture capitalists.
docs.snippet: The swelling market for property technology to help buy, sell and manage properties has attracted building owners as well as venture capitalists.
docs.lead_paragraph: When executives at Rudin Management Company started looking for an operating system in 2009 to help them manage their building portfolio, the market for property technology was still in its infancy, and they came up empty-handed.

headline.main: Seeking an Edge, Developers and Investors Turn to ‘Proptech’
headline.print_headline: A Tech Revolution in Managing Properties

docs.abstract: The financier Michael Milken is a major investor in a property that became eligible for a federal tax break — after his longtime friend, Steven Mnuchin, intervened.
docs.snippet: The financier Michael Milken is a major investor in a property that became eligible for a federal tax break — after his longtime friend, Steven Mnuchin, intervened.
docs.lead_paragraph: RENO, Nev. — In the 1980s, Michael Milken embodied Wall Street greed. A swashbuckling financier, he was charged with playing a central role in a vast insider-trading scheme and was sent to prison for violating federal securities and tax laws. He was an inspiration for the Gordon Gekko character in the film “Wall Street.”

headline.main: Symbol of ’80s Greed Stands to Profit From Trump Tax Break for Poor Areas
headline.print_headline: Junk Bond King’ in Line To Profit From Tax Breaks

docs.abstract: Speaking for the first time publicly about his longtime ties to the disgraced financier, Leslie Wexner condemned deceptions by “people who have secret lives.”
docs.snippet: Speaking for the first time publicly about his longtime ties to the disgraced financier, Leslie Wexner condemned deceptions by “people who have secret lives.”
docs.lead_paragraph: With investors and analysts gathered in Columbus, Ohio, on Tuesday for a day of presentations and store tours by the company that owns Victoria’s Secret and Bath & Body Works, Leslie H. Wexner, its chief executive and founder, spoke publicly for the first time about his longtime ties to Jeffrey Epstein.

headline.main: Epstein Looms Over Speech by Billionaire Behind Victoria’s Secret
headline.print_headline: Billionaire Tied to Epstein Speaks of Being Betrayed
